upo.graph

Interface GraphSearchResult

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<Vertex>

    public interface GraphSearchResult
extends java.lang.Iterable<Vertex>
    The interface describing the result of a visit in a Graph.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      double getDistance(Vertex v)
      For BFS and Dikstra search types, this method returns the distance (i.e., the length/weight of the shortest path between the source vertex S and v.
      double getEdgeWeight(Vertex v1, Vertex v2)
      Returns the weight of the edge between v1 and v2 in the current search result, if it exists.
      int getEndTime(Vertex v)
      Returns the visit time (where the first time is 1) in which the target vertex v was closed in the current visit (i.e., when v became black).
      Vertex getParentOf(Vertex v)
      Returns the parent of the target vertex v in the search tree/forest.
      Vertex getSource()
      Returns the source vertex S of the search which generates this result
      int getStartTime(Vertex v)
      Returns the visit time (where the first time is 1) in which the target vertex v was discovered in the current visit (i.e., when v became gray).
      SearchType getType()
      Returns the type of the search (e.g., BFS) which generates this result

      • getDistance

        double getDistance(Vertex v)
            throws java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException,
                   java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        For BFS and Dikstra search types, this method returns the distance (i.e., the length/weight of the shortest path between the source vertex S and v. If v is not reachable from S, this method returns Double.POSITIVE_INFINITY. If v does not belong to the visited Graph, it throws an IllegalArgumentException. For other visit types, it throws an UnsupportedOperationException.
        Parameters:
        v - the target vertex.
        Returns:
        \delta(S,v)
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if v does not belong to the graph.
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - if this.getType() is different from BFS and DIJKSTRA

      • getParentOf

        Vertex getParentOf(Vertex v)
            throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Returns the parent of the target vertex v in the search tree/forest. If v is the root of a tree, this method returns null . If v does not belong to the visited Graph, it throws an IllegalArgumentException.
        Parameters:
        v - the target vertex.
        Returns:
        the parent of v in the current search.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if v does not belong to the graph.

      • getStartTime

        int getStartTime(Vertex v)
          throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Returns the visit time (where the first time is 1) in which the target vertex v was discovered in the current visit (i.e., when v became gray). If v was not discovered, this method returns -1. If v does not belong to the visited Graph, it throws an IllegalArgumentException.
        Parameters:
        v - the target vertex.
        Returns:
        the time in which v was discovered.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if v does not belong to the graph.

      • getEndTime

        int getEndTime(Vertex v)
        throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Returns the visit time (where the first time is 1) in which the target vertex v was closed in the current visit (i.e., when v became black). If v was not discovered, this method returns -1. If v does not belong to the visited Graph, it throws an IllegalArgumentException.
        Parameters:
        v - the target vertex.
        Returns:
        the time in which v was closed.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if v does not belong to the graph.

      • getEdgeWeight

        double getEdgeWeight(Vertex v1,
                     Vertex v2)
              throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Returns the weight of the edge between v1 and v2 in the current search result, if it exists. Otherwise, it returns an IllegalArgumentException. If v1 and/or v2 do not belong to the visited Graph, it throws an IllegalArgumentException.
        Parameters:
        v1 - the parent vertex.
        v2 - the child vertex
        Returns:
        the weight of the edge (v1,v2).
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if v1 or v2 do not belong to the graph.
